<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,758,1326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,758,783]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Crown approximately quadrangular, with two pairs of orange maculae, one close to anterior margin and another close to posterior margin, adjacent to compound eyes (
<figureCitation box="[899,969,794,818]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[956,969,794,818]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); transverse carina present at transition between crown and frons (
<figureCitation box="[448,548,830,854]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Figs 
<number box="[505,548,830,854]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="2.3">2, 3</number>
</figureCitation>
); ocelli on anterior margin of head, at transition between crown and frons (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,166,866,890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
); clypeus with lateral margins convergent apically (
<figureCitation box="[766,837,866,890]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[821,837,866,890]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
); posterior margin of pronotum emarginated and Vshaped (
<figureCitation box="[246,314,902,926]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[301,314,902,926]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
); forewings with venation indistinct or slightly distinct with four apical cells and three anteapical cells (
<figureCitation box="[217,286,938,962]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[269,286,938,962]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
); hindwings with R 
<number box="[504,512,954,968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[521,528,954,968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="5.0">5</number>
and M 
<number box="[604,610,954,968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<number box="[619,628,954,968]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="2.0">2</number>
preapically convergent, fused at apex, forming single vein. Male genitalia. Pygofer without processes or teeth (
<figureCitation box="[614,685,977,1001]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[669,685,977,1001]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
); connective variable, bifurcated or not at articulation point with aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[270,338,1013,1037]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[323,338,1013,1037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
); aedeagus long with pair(s) of apical or preapical process(es) or lamellae (
<figureCitation box="[1193,1311,1013,1037]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Figs 
<number box="[1251,1311,1013,1037]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="9.1">9, 10</number>
</figureCitation>
); anal tube with pair of variable basal processes (
<figureCitation box="[599,670,1049,1073]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[656,670,1049,1073]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques-Costa" box="[690,1111,1049,1073]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" refString="Marques-Costa, A. P. &amp; R. R. Cavichioli. (2008) Tetralidia gen. nov., a new neotropical genus of Neocoelidiinae (Hemiptera, Cicadellidae). Zootaxa, 1892, 26 - 34." type="journal article" year="2008">
Marques-Costa &amp; Cavichioli (
<number box="[1042,1104,1049,1073]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="2008.0">2008</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
; subgenital plates narrowed basally or pre-apically, separated only in most distal portion of apex (
<figureCitation box="[930,998,1085,1109]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Fig. 
<number box="[983,998,1085,1109]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
) and style with truncated apex (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 10" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[214,1374,225,1843]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[206,1375,223,1875]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 10. Tetralidia curvipenis sp. nov., male holotype: 1, head, pronotum and mesonotum, dorsal view; 2, head, frontal view; 3, head, pronotum and mesonotum, lateral view; 4, forewing; 5, pygofer and anal tube, lateral view; 6, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 7, style, lateral view; 8, connective and styles, dorsal view; 9, aedeagus, lateral view; 10, aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/279025/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Figs 
<number pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="7.8">7, 8</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="24" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,758,1326]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName box="[197,306,1157,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tetralidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[197,306,1157,1181]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Tetralidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Kramer, 1964" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1964" box="[520,762,1157,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tozzita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[520,598,1158,1181]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Tozzita</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer" box="[606,762,1157,1181]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1964) A generic revision of the leafhopper subfamily Neocoelidiinae. (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Proceedings of the United States National Museum, 15, 259 - 287." type="journal article" year="1964">
Kramer, 
<quantity box="[706,762,1157,1181]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.98856" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" unit="in" value="1964.0">1964</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in having the clypeus with lateral margins convergent apically; the pygofer without processes; the aedeagus long and the anal tube with a pair of basal processes. It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[212,290,1230,1253]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tozzita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[212,290,1230,1253]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Tozzita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of a black spot at the apex of the crown; the ocelli on the transition between crown and frons (in 
<taxonomicName box="[253,331,1266,1289]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Tozzita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[253,331,1266,1289]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Tozzita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
located on the crown, near the anterior margin) and the pygofer with a rounded apex (flattened and spatulate in 
<emphasis box="[286,378,1303,1326]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Tozzoita</emphasis>
) Marques-Costa (
<number box="[581,642,1301,1325]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="2008.0">2008</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
